extends layout

block content
    .jumbotron
        .container
            <h1>Easy Genome Aligner<br><small>Here you can align multiple genome sequences like a breeze.</small></h1>
            p Multiple genome alignments play a fundamental role in many biological realms such as evolution and genomics.
            p Easy Genome Aligner (EGA), a set of tools implemented into a software package, is designed to make complicated whole genome multiple alignments really accessible for most biologists.
            <br>
            a.btn.btn-primary.btn-lg(role="button" href="http://egateam.github.io/1.html") Learn more »

    .row.container
        .col-xs-1
            <p></p>
        .col-xs-5
            .text-center
                <img src="/images/EGA_E.jpg" alt="Yeast" style="width: 180px; height: 200px;">
                <h2>Multiple genome alignments</h2>
                <p>Help you to obtain phylogenetic relationship and genetic variation information among multiple genomes.</p>
                <p><a role="button" href="http://egateam.github.io/21.html"  class="btn btn-default">View details »</a></p>
        .col-xs-5
            .text-center
                <img src="/images/EGA_G.jpg" alt="Paralog detection" class="img-circle" style="width: 200px; height: 200px;">
                <h2>Self-alignment</h2>
                <p>Help you to detect paralogs and obtain best-to-best pairwise alignment.</p>
                <p><a role="button" href="http://egateam.github.io/22.html" class="btn btn-default">View details »</a></p>

    hr.featurette-divider

    .container
        .row.col-xs-2
        .row.col-xs-2
            h1 Aligner
    .container
        .row.col-xs-2
        .row.col-xs-8.text-center
            .container.row
                .col-xs-4.bor
                    <h4><a title="bacteria" href="http://egateam.github.io/32.html">Inter-species Alignment</a></h4>
                    <br>
                    <p><a href="http://egateam.github.io/32.html"><img class="pull-left img-rounded pic" src="/images/Ecoli.jpg" alt="bacteria" width="120" height="115"></a>Through multiple genome alignment, you can obtain phylogenetic relationship of multiple species. Here we take 20 bacteria genomes as an example .</p>
                    <br>
                .col-xs-4.bor
                    <h4><a title="Services" href="http://egateam.github.io/31.html">Intra-species Alignment</a></h4>
                    <br>
                    <p><a href="http://egateam.github.io/31.html"><img class="pull-left img-rounded pic" src="/images/yeast.jpg" alt="services" width="120" height="120"></a>You can also use multiple genome alignmnet to analyze re-sequenced genomes for population genetic inference. Here we take 12 yeast genomes as an example.</p>

            .container.row
                .col-xs-4.bor
                    <h4><a title="Deposits" href="http://egateam.github.io/33.html">Paralog Detction</a></h4>
                    <br>
                    <p><a href="http://egateam.github.io/33.html"><img class="pull-left img-thumbnail pic" src="/images/paralog.png" alt="deposit" width="120" height="120"></a>You can detect paralogs by self-alignment and obtain best-to-best pairwise similar sequences. Here we use yeast strain S288c as an example.<br>
                    </p>
                    <br>
                .col-xs-4.bor
                    <h4><a title="Research" href="http://egateam.github.io/4.html">Local Alignment tool</a></h4>
                    <br>
                    <p><a href="http://egateam.github.io/4.html"><img class="pull-left img-thumbnail pic" src="/images/virtual_box.png" alt="research" width="120" height="120"></a>for those who need to deal with large-scale data, we also provide local operation tool with all required dependencies integrated into a virtual machine.<br>
                    </p>
